mx.unam.fciencias.binio

Class BinFile

  • java.lang.Object
    • mx.unam.fciencias.binio.BinFile

  • public class BinFile
extends java.lang.Object
    Provides access to files in binary mode. The user can read/write the file bit by bit or byte by byte.
    Version:
    3.0
    april 2015
    Author:

    • Method Detail

      • close

        public void close()
           throws BinIOException
        Close the file. Flush the buffer to disk if the file was open for writing.
        Throws:
        BinIOException - if the operation cannot be completed.

      • endOfBinFile

        public boolean endOfBinFile()
        Check if the end of file is been reached. Further reads will throw an exception after this method returns true.
        Returns:
        true if the end of file is reached, false in other case.

      • getSize

        public long getSize()
        Returns the file size. If the instance is an input file returns the total number of bytes available in file for reading. Otherwise returns the number of bytes written.
        Returns:
        file size in bytes.

      • main

        public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)
        Testing program. Copy a file into another.
        Parameters:
        args - input and output filenames must be given in command line, the input file first.

      • open

        public void open(java.lang.String fname,
                 int mode)
          throws BinIOException
        Open the file to be read or write.
        Parameters:
        fname - file name.
        mode - access mode:
        • BinFile.INPUT for reading.
        • BinFile.OUTPUT for writing.
        Throws:
        BinIOException - If:
        • Input file not found.
        • Input file cannot be open for reading.
        • Invalid mode value.

      • readBit

        public boolean readBit()
                throws BinIOException
        Reads the next bit in the input file.
        Returns:
        true if the read bit value is 1. false otherwise.
        Throws:
        BinIOException - if you attempt to read beyond the end of file or some other I/O error occurs.

      • readByte

        public byte readByte()
              throws BinIOException
        Reads the next complete byte in the input file. If the previous reading operation was a readBit and a byte was not readed completely by that method, the residual bits of previous byte are not accessible anymore. The user must read the byte completely bit by bit if data lost is not desired.
        Returns:
        the byte that was read.
        Throws:
        BinIOException - if you attempt to read beyond the end of file or some other I/O error occurs.

      • readInt

        public int readInt(boolean little)
            throws BinIOException
        Reads an integer (int type) from file, the byte ordering is specified.
        Parameters:
        little - specifies the byte ordering convention to be used: little-endian if true, big-endian otherwise.
        Returns:
        the integer value read.
        Throws:
        BinIOException - if you attempt to read beyond the end of file or some other I/O error occurs.

      • writeBit

        public void writeBit(boolean bitvalue)
              throws BinIOException
        Write the next bit in the output file.
        Parameters:
        bitvalue - true means 1, false means 0.
        Throws:
        BinIOException - in case of some I/O error.

      • writeByte

        public void writeByte(byte b)
               throws BinIOException
        Write the next byte in the output file.
        Parameters:
        b - the byte to be written
        Throws:
        BinIOException - if the buffer is full and cannot be flushed to disk.

      • writeInt

        public void writeInt(int num,
                     boolean little)
              throws BinIOException
        Write an int in file, byte order (endianess) is specified. Four bytes is the assumed size for an integer.
        Parameters:
        num - the integer to be written
        little - specifies the byte ordering convention to be used: little-endian if true; big-endian otherwise.
        Throws:
        BinIOException - if the buffer is full and cannot be flushed to disk.
